Cutar HIV / AIDS: Kasar Sin Ta Yi Rahoton Hawan Sabbin Mutane Da Kashi 14
Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Hukumar kiwon lafiya ta kasar Sin ta ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar.
Kusan sabbin mutane 40,000 ne aka samu a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin waɗanda suke da cutar sun kamu ne ta wurin jima'i, kuma wannan sabon abu ne.
A tarihi, cutar ta bazu cikin sauri a wasu yankuna na ƙasar ta hanyar ƙarin jini da ke da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000 a shekara.
A cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin, kamuwa da cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce.
An haramta luwadi a China a 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga LGBT har yanzu yana da yawa.
Domin halin da ake ciki a ƙasar, wasu bincike sun nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke luwadi suna yin aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka na kamuwa da cutar suna faruwa ne domin rashin kāriya na jima'i.
A matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin da ake yi na magance wannan matsalar, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV ga dukan mutane tun shekara ta 2003.
