A ranar Lahadi ne fadar White House ta sanar da cewa za a iya jinkirta taron da ke da muhimmanci tsakanin Donald Trump da mataimakin babban lauya Rod Rosenstein har mako guda, yayin da ake ci gaba da gwagwarmayar neman takarar kotun koli Brett Kavanaugh.
Rosenstein na kula da aikin Robert Mueller, mai ba da shawara na musamman da ke binciken tsoma bakin Rasha a zaben, alaƙar da ke tsakanin abokan aikin Trump da Rasha, da kuma yiwuwar cikas da shugaban ke yi wa shari'a.
Tambayar ko Trump zai kori mataimakin babban lauyan, kuma hakan zai sa 'yancin Mueller ya zama cikin hadari, ya kasance yana ta zubo jita-jita a Washington na tsawon watanni.
A farkon wannan watan, jaridar New York Times ta ruwaito cewa Rosenstein ya yi magana game da saka makirufo domin ya yi rikodin tattaunawar da Trump ke yi da kuma yiwuwar kawar da shugaban kasa ta hanyar gyara na 25.
Rosenstein ya musanta wannan zargin.
Amma a ranar Litinin da ta gabata, ya bayyana a fadar White House, a lokacin da yake gab da yin murabus.
Maimakon haka, an sanar da ganawa da Trump, wanda a lokacin yana Majalisar Dinkin Duniya a birnin New York, a ranar Alhamis.
Trump ya ce zai fi son kada ya kori Mr. Rosenstein, amma an dage taron domin kaucewa fuskantarwa da sauraron kwamitin shari'a na majalisar dattawa wanda Kavanaugh da Dr. Christine Blasey Ford suka shaida, daya daga cikin matan da suka zarge shi da cin zarafin mata.
A ranar Juma'a, Trump ya umarci hukumar FBI da ta gudanar da bincike na mako guda kan karar da aka shigar kan Kavanaugh, har ma ya jinkirta zaben majalisar dattawa.
A ranar Lahadi, wakilin yada labaran Trump, Sarah Sanders, ta bayyana a Fox News.
